In this configuration:
- The `google_compute_instance_template` resource is used to define the web app instance template.
- `google_compute_autoscaler` manages the automatic scaling of instances based on CPU utilization.
- `google_compute_instance_group` represents instances managed by the autoscaler.
- `google_compute_region_instance_name` is set up as a target pool to help smooth traffic circulation across instances. 

These resources are configured to automate the scaling of web app instances to ensure that the setup can handle varying loads efficiently.

