response:
To create an AWS CodeBuild project resource definition in Terraform with a sample IAM role and build batch configuration, you can define the necessary resources using HCL (HashiCorp Configuration Language). Below is the configuration you can use as a starting point:

```hcl
resource "aws_iam_role" "codestar" {
  name               = "codestar-build-role"
  assume_role_policy = <<EOF
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Service": "codebuild.amazonaws.com"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
    }
  ]
}
EOF
}

resource "aws_codebuild_project" "example" {
  name              = "example-codebuild"
  description       = "A sample codebuild project"
  build_timeout    = 5
  service_role_arn = aws_iam_role.codestar.arn

  artifacts {
    type = "NO_ARTIFACTS"
  }

  environment {
    compute_type    = "PROVISIONED_BUILD_SERVER"
    image           = "aws/codebuild/standard:4.0"
    type            = "Linux"
  }
}
```

### Explanation:
- **`aws_iam_role`**: Defines an IAM role with a trust policy allowing AWS CodeBuild to assume the role.
- **`aws_codebuild_project`**: Specifies the CodeBuild project configuration including the IAM role to use, project description, build timeout, artifact type, and the build environment details.

Remember to modify the parameters and configurations based on your specific requirements and ensure that your AWS provider is correctly set up.

