  create_version = true
  description = "Types of pizza available to order"
  name = "PizzaTypes"
  enumeration_value {
    value = "Margherita"
  }
  enumeration_value {
    value = "Pepperoni"
  }
}

response:
To create an AWS Lex bot for pizza ordering using Terraform, you can define the resources for a Bot, Bot Alias, and language model. Additionally, if you want a specific follow-up prompt, you'll need to create intents or slot types using AWS Lambda functions or AWS Lambda with AWS Lex or AWS Lex Development Bot Editor through AWS SDKs, as this is typically handled outside of Terraform.

Here’s the Terraform configuration for setting up AWS Lex resources:

```hcl
resource "aws_lex_bot" "pizza_ordering_bot" {
  name               = "PizzaOrderingBot"
  description        = "Bot designed for pizza ordering"
  locale            = "en-US"
  child_directories = [] # Bot root directory, specify if you have subdirectories
}

resource "aws_lex_intent" "order_intent" {
  bot_id            = aws_lex_bot.pizza_ordering_bot.id
  bot_version      = aws_lex_bot.pizza_ordering_bot.version
  b_slot_types {
    name           = "OrderType"
    description    = "The type of pizza order to be placed"
  }
  b_locales {
    locale         = "en-US"
    content {
      intent       = "Order"
      description  = "Intent to order pizza"
    }
  }
}

resource "aws_lex_bot_alias" "pizza_ordering_alias" {
  bot_id         = aws_lex_bot.pizza_ordering_bot.id
  bot_version   = aws_lex_bot.pizza_ordering_bot.version
  alias_name     = "PizzaOrderingAlias"
  description   = "Alias for deployed pizza ordering bot"
  b_slots {         # Again this requires subsequent external setup
    name             = "OrderType"
    description     = "The slot for pizza order type"
  }
  b_locales {
    locale         = "en-US"
    content {        # This requires being prepared similar to what was previously created
      bot_alias_id = "order_intent"
    }
  }
}
```

This configuration establishes the foundational structure of a Lex bot, defining the intent and bot alias. The follow-up prompts will be constructed using AWS SDK through external processes, as Terraform is primarily an infrastructure-as-code tool without direct command structure definitions.

