To create an Amazon Kinesis Data Firehose delivery stream configured to use an extended Amazon S3 destination using Terraform, we'll need to define the resources necessary for both the Firehose delivery stream and the S3 bucket that will serve as the destination. Here is the Terraform configuration to achieve that:

```hcl
resource "aws_kinesis_firehose_delivery_stream" "example" {
  name                        = "example-delivery-stream"
  s3_configuration {
    role_arn     = aws_iam_role.example.arn
    bucket_arn    = aws_s3_bucket.example.arn
    topic_arn    = aws_sns_topic.example.arn
    prefix       = "example/"
    buffering_hduration = "60"
  }
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "example" {
  bucket = "example-extended-destination"
}

resource "aws_sns_topic" "example" {
  name = "example-extended-sns-topic"
}

resource "aws_iam_role" "example" {
  name = "example-s3-role"
  assume_role_policy {
    // Policy details here
  }
}
```

In this configuration:
- A Kinesis Firehose delivery stream (`aws_kinesis_firehose_delivery_stream`) is defined with an S3 configuration that specifies an S3 bucket and an SNS topic.
- The AWS IAM Role (`aws_iam_role`) is configured to provide permissions for making the Kinesis data-streams to apply Amazon Kinesis Conversions data conventions and to manage interacting with the S3 bucket.
- The activity of Kinesis Firehose can be routed by using the SNS topic (`aws_sns_topic`) intended to handle extended S3 notification destinations.

Make sure to replace the placeholder values with actual ARNs and policies suitable for your use case.

