Below is the HCL code block for a simple Amazon Kinesis Data Analytics V2 application using Terraform. This configuration sets up an application for SQL-based analytics and includes basic parameters.

```hcl
resource "aws_kinesis_analytics_application" "example" {
  name        = "example-kinesis-analytics-app"
  type        = "EXTERNAL"

  kinesis_analytics_application_configuration {
    application_code_configuration {
      code_content {
        s3_content_location {
          bucket_name   = "your-s3-bucket-name"
          resource_key  = "your-sql-code-key"
        }

        compute resources {
          code_dependencies {
            role_arn   = "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/YourRole"
            execution_role {
              role_arn = "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/service-role/YourExecutionRole"
            }
          }

          runtime_configuration {
            node_type              = "SGXLINUX_2.0" // For SQL-based applications, use the line of service provided by AWS
            processor_count       = 2
            runtime_environment = "LAMBDA"
          }
        }
      }
    }

    application_configuration {
      arithmetic_dependencies {
        input {
          name_positive = "exampleInput"
          input_schema {
            record_encoding = "JSON"
            record_encoding = "UTF-8"
            record_columns {
              name      = "field1"
              data_type = "INTEGER"
            }
          }
        }
      }

      environment_properties {
        resource_type = "DBTABLE"
        property_groups {
          property_group {
            properties {
              property_name     = "metrics"
              property_value   = "example"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This configuration includes the basic setup of a Kinesis Data Analytics V2 application aimed at handling SQL-based analytics. Make sure to replace placeholders with actual values like `your-s3-bucket-name` and `your-sql-code-key` with appropriate details for your SQL application and IAM roles/ARNs. Adjust input configuration and other SSH parameters according to your application’s requirements.

