response:
To create an AWS IAM role for use with Amazon EKS Fargate profiles, you need to define the role and set up a trust policy that allows it to be assumed by `eks-fargate-pods.amazonaws.com`. Additionally, you should attach the managed policy for EKS Fargate Pod execution. Here's the Terraform configuration in HCL format:

```hcl
resource "aws_iam_role" "eks_fargate_profile_example" {
  name = "eks-fargate-profile-example"

  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({
    Version = "2012-10-17"
    Statement = [
      {
        Effect = "Allow"
        Principal = {
          Service = "eks-fargate-pods.amazonaws.com"
        }
        Action = "sts:AssumeRole"
      }
    ]
  })

  managed_policy {
    name = "arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonEKSFargatePodExecutionRole"
  }
}
```

This configuration creates an IAM role with the required trust policy and attaches the `AmazonEKSFargatePodExecutionRole` managed policy for the role to interact with EKS Fargate pods.

