}
```

This configuration creates an S3 bucket with the appropriate versioning and object lock settings in compliance mode, targeting object lock settings to the same bucket. The `force_destroy` attribute facilitates cleanup in cases where the bucket may need to be destroyed without manual deletion of its contents first. Note that, in the latest Terraform AWS provider versions, the object lock rule could be explicitly configured inside the `object_lock` block, and `sse_kms_key_id` would typically require an actual KMS key ID if Server-Side Encryption with a KMS Key is required, instead of setting it to `null`.

