To set up an AWS DynamoDB Contributor Insights resource with a tailored configuration using Terraform, you'll define the DynamoDB table and configure the Contributor Insights resource for it. Here's the Terraform configuration:

```hcl
resource "aws_dynamodb_table" "example" {
  name           = "example-table"
  attributes {
    name = "id"
    type = "S"
  }
  hash_key = "id"
  billing_mode = "PAY_PER_REQUEST"

  read_capacity = 5
  write_capacity = 5
}

resource "aws_dynamodb_table_contributor_insights" "example" {
  table_name = aws_dynamodb_table.example.name
  retention_period {
    days = 15
  }
  sampling_percentage {
    value = 60 // Tailor the sampling percentage as needed
  }
}
```

In this configuration, you define an `aws_dynamodb_table` with key attributes and capacity settings, followed by a `aws_dynamodb_table_contributor_insights` resource. Generating the DynamoDB Contributor Insights report with specific customization options like retention period and sampling percentage. Adjust values and attributes based on actual requirements.

