  name = "msk-cluster-${random_id.cluster_id.hex}"
  region = "us-east1"
  location = "us-east1"
  kafka_version = "2.2.0"
  topics = [
    {
      name        = "topic1"
      display_name = "Default Topic"
    },
    {
      name        = "topic2"
      display_name = "Default Topic"
    }
  ]
  storage = "googlecloud"
  storage_bucket = aws_s3_bucket.log_bucket.id

  producer_id = google_cloud_build.msk_build.id
  producer_id = google_cloud_build.msk_build.id
}

output "msk_cluster_id" {
  value = google_messaging.msk_cluster.name
}
```

This configuration establishes a Managed Streaming for Apache Kafka (MSK) cluster in the Google Cloud with the `us-east1` region and configures logging to an AWS S3 bucket. It introduces random IDs for cluster and log file identifiers to avoid naming conflicts. KMS keys on AWS are used for S3 bucket encryption, and Cloud Build is utilized with placeholder arguments for deployment steps, ensuring logs are sent to the S3 bucket for storage. Adjust configurations based on your specific Kafka and AWS S3 settings as needed.

