Below is the Terraform configuration in HCL format for setting up an Amazon DynamoDB table with global replicas in the specified regions:

```hcl
resource "aws_dynamodb_table" "example" {
  name           = "globalReplicaTable"
  hash_key    = "id"
  range_key   = "range"
  read_capacity = 5
  write_capacity = 5
  billing_mode = "PROVISIONED"

  attribute {
    name = "id"
    type = "S"
  }

  attribute {
    name = "range"
    type = "N"
  }

  replica {
    region_name = "us-east-2"
    global_secondary_index {
      name = "GlobalIndex"
      hash_key = "id"
      projection_type = "ALL"
    }
  }

  replica {
    region_name = "us-west-2"
    global_secondary_index {
      name = "GlobalIndex"
      hash_key = "id"
      projection_type = "ALL"
    }
}
```

This configuration sets up an Amazon DynamoDB table named `globalReplicaTable` with global replicas in the `us-east-2` and `us-west-2` regions and defines an attribute and a global secondary index for these regions. Choosen hash keys and read/write capacities should be adjusted according to your requirement.

