response:
To set up a personalized TTL (Time-to-Live) field for managing data expiration, you can use AWS DynamoDB with TTL. Here's how you can configure it using Terraform:

```hcl
resource "aws_dynamodb_table" "example" {
  name           = "example-table"
  billing_mode   = "PROVISIONED"
  read_capacity  = 5
  write_capacity = 5
  hash_key       = "id"

  attribute {
    name = "id"
    type = "S"
  }

  ttl {
    attribute_name = "TTL"
    enabled        = true
  }
}
```

In this configuration, we have set up a DynamoDB table named `example-table` with a TTL attribute `TTL`. The TTL attribute should be a timestamp in Unix epoch format (seconds since 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z), which defines when the items will expire.

