response:
To set up an AWS Chime Voice Connector and provision a logging configuration for recording only media metrics, you can create the following Terraform configuration:

```hcl
resource "aws_chime_voice_connector" "example_connector" {
  name        = "example-chime-voice-connector"
  metadata    = "Voice connector metadata"
  configuration = {
    permissions  = "[{"communications-service-type":"media_metrics"}]"
  }
}

resource "aws_chime_voice_connector_logging_configuration" "example_logging" {
  voice_connector_id = aws_chime_voice_connector.example_connector.id
  recording_setting = "Always"
  destination  = {
    service = "media_metrics"
  }
}
```

This configuration creates a voice connector and then sets up logging to record media metrics only. The logging configuration specifies the destination service as `media_metrics`. Ensure that your AWS provider configuration includes permissions to manage logging and allow only media metrics recording when setting up permissions and roles.

