To set up an Amazon Chime Voice Connector with encryption using media metrics logging through Terraform, you need to use both `chime_voice_connector` and `chime_voice_connector_logging_configuration` resources. Here's how the configuration might look in HCL:

```hcl
resource "aws_chime_voice_connector" "example" {
  name = "example-connector"
  uri  = "example-connector-uri"
  encryption_specification {
    encryption_key = "example-key" // This key should be configured according to AWS Chime requirements
  }
}

resource "aws_chime_voice_connector_logging_configuration" "example" {
  voice_connector_id         = aws_chime_voice_connector.example.id
  endpoint_configuration {
    vpn_security {
      vpn_endpoint_region               = "us-west-2" // Example region
      record_calls                      = true
      record_calls_ongoing_conversations = true
    }
  } 
}
```

In this configuration, you set up an Amazon Chime Voice Connector with encryption enabled and configure media metrics logging to record ongoing conversations and calls. Make sure to replace placeholders with actual values based on your setup for encryption keys and logging specifications.

