In this configuration, an EC2 instance named `example_instance` is launched under AWS EC2 service with the AMI ID signifying the base image used to launch the instance. The `aws_backup_vault` resource serves as a container that facilitates the backup management by AWS Backup service. 

The `aws_backup_plan` resource specifies the backup rules, including the scheduling of backups to take place daily at 12:00 AM. The lifecycle rules defined ensure backups are deleted after 30 days. The backup is automatically initiated for the specified resources in the AWS Backup plan.

Finally, `aws_backup_selection` defines the EC2 instance to be backed up along with the permissions or role required to carry out the operation. 

You will need to fill in specifics like AMI IDs, AWS Backup role ARN, and any parameters relevant to your specific resources and backup plans for this to be functional.

