To provision an AWS RDS PostgreSQL 15 database using Terraform for executing Airbyte connector tests with specific configurations, we'll use the provided examples format. Here's the HCL code for provisioning the database along with the subnets. Note that we assume the subnets are pre-defined in the public subnet IDs `subnet-1, subnet-2, etc.` for the designated availability zones.

```hcl
resource "random_password" "db_password" {
  length  = 16
  special = false
}

resource "aws_db_instance" "airbyte_test_db" {
  identifier                   = "airbyte-test-db"
  allocated_storage            = 5 // in Gigabytes,
  instance_class              = "db.t3.micro"
  engine                     = "postgres"
  engine_version             = "15"
  availability_zone          = "${var.public_subnets.0}-${aws_region.current.name}"
  storage_type                = "gp2"
  username                   = "airbyte"
  password                   = random_password.db_password.result
  skip_final_snapshot        = true
  db_subnet_group_name       = aws_db_subnet_group.test.id
  vpc_security_groups        = [aws_security_group.test.id]
  multi_az                   = false
  backup_retention_period    = 0
}

resource "aws_security_group" "test_sg" {
  name        = "airbyte-test-sg"
  description = "Security group for RDS PostgreSQL database for Airbyte tests"
  vpc_id      = aws_vpc.test.id

  ingress {
    from_port   = "5432"
    to_port     = "5432"
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }

  egress {
    from_port   = "0"
    to_port     = "0"
    protocol    = "-1"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }
}

resource "aws_db_subnet_group" "test" {
  name       = "airbyte-test-sg"
  subnet_ids  = [aws_subnet.test.id1, aws_subnet.test.id2]

  tags = {
    Name = "PostgreSQLTestSubnetGroup"
  }
}

resource "aws_vpc" "test" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
  // Other properties would be defined as per existing infrastructure setup
}

resource "aws_subnet" "test" {
  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.test.id
  cidr_block         = "${var.public_subnets.0}"
  availability_zone  = "us-west-2a"

  tags = {
    Name = "TestSubnet1"
  }

  vpc_tags = {
    Name = "TestSubnet2"
  }
}

resource "aws_subnet" "test" {
  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.test.id
  cidr_block         = "${var.public_subnets.1}"
  availability_zone  = "us-west-2b"

  tags = {
    Name = "TestSubnet3"
  }

  vpc_tags = {
    Name = "TestSubnet4"
  }
}
```

In this configuration, we define a security group and a subnet group for our test database instance. The `aws_db_instance` resource defines an RDS instance for PostgreSQL 15 using the specified instance class and storage type. This assumes you have defined your VPC and available subnets. Adjust `subnet_ids` accordingly with actual IDs for your designated subnets.

Please ensure all required variables and data are filled in with actual values owned by your infrastructure. The security group ingress and egress rules may also require modification to ensure proper security alignment for your tests.

