To manage an AWS Lightsail distribution with an S3 bucket as its origin, you'll need to configure a distribution and specify an S3 bucket as the origin. Below is a Terraform configuration for setting up such a distribution:

```hcl
resource "aws_lightsail_distribution" "example" {
  name                     = "example-distribution"
  content_type             = "binary/octet-stream"
  dns_name                = "example.com"
  comment                = "Example distribution"
  enabled                = true

  origin {
    s3 {
      s3_bucket_regional_origin_id = "example-s3-bucket-region-id"
    }
  }

  cache_refresh {
    origin_id = aws_lightsail_distribution.example.origin[0].s3.id
    paths      = "/*"
    ttl_seconds = 604800
  }

  logging_config {
    bucket = "example-logging-bucket.s3.amazonaws.com"
    overwrite = false
    include_cookies = false
  }
}

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "origin_bucket" {
  bucket = "example-s3-bucket"
  region = "us-west-2"
}
```

Make sure to replace placeholders like `"example-distribution"` and `"example-s3-bucket"` with your actual distribution and S3 bucket names, and adjust the `s3_bucket_regional_origin_id` and other parameters according to your specific configuration.

