response:
Here's the Terraform configuration for provisioning an AWS VPC in the `us-east-2` region using a specified CIDR range, and attaching an Internet Gateway to it with the required tags:

```hcl
resource "aws_vpc" "example" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
  tags = {
    Name = "vpc"
  }
}

resource "aws_internet_gateway" "example" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.example.id
  tags = {
    Name = "ig"
  }
}

resource "aws_route" "internet_access" {
  route_table_id         = aws_vpc.example.main_route_table_id
  destination_cidr_block = "0.0.0.0/0"
  gateway_id            = aws_internet_gateway.example.id
}
```

In this code, an AWS VPC with the specified CIDR block in `us-east-2` is created. An Internet Gateway is attached to the VPC and tagged with "ig". The route table of the VPC is also modified to allow internet access through the Internet Gateway. You can customize the `cidr_block` as per your requirement. Additionally, you can add other resources and configurations to the VPC based on your specific needs.

